newsitem.title: VIETNAM: Vietnam Jan-Oct industry output up yr-yr 13.5 pct.
newsitem.headline: Vietnam Jan-Oct industry output up yr-yr 13.5 pct.

text.p: Vietnam's industrial output rose 13.5 percent in January-October this year from a year earlier, the Government Statistics Office said on Tuesday.
Figures showed state-sector output rose 11.8 percent, non-state 12.9 percent and foreign-owned 18.9 percent.
Industrial output in October alone was 13.6 percent higher than in the same month last year.
Industrial output in the first nine months of this year was up 13.5 percent from the same period a year earlier.
Comparative figures for production growth in the first ten months of 1995 were not immediately available but trends in recent months have pointed to a slight slowing in the pace of growth.
